<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 08 at 2:59PM EDT  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Macomb
and east central St. Clair Counties through 345 PM EDT...
At 259 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Richmond, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
St. Clair around 325 PM EDT.
Other locations impacted by this storm include Adair, Rattle Run and
New Haven.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
